Differential diagnosis. 
<taxonomicName id="4C294D18FFA7E27A34EEABA3FD61FF26" authorityName=": Bily" authorityYear="1985" box="[460,728,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="529" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="komareki" subGenus="Haplanthaxia">
<emphasis id="B95DEA89FFA7E27A34EEABA3FD88FF26" box="[460,561,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="529">Anthaxia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B95DEA89FFA7E27A3761ABA3FDE6FF27" box="[579,607,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="529">H.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B95DEA89FFA7E27A3753ABA3FD61FF26" box="[625,728,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="529">komareki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the very similar species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C294D18FFA7E27A31ADABA3FAFCFF26" authorityName="Kerremans" authorityYear="1898" box="[1167,1349,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="529" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pilifrons" subGenus="Haplanthaxia">
<emphasis id="B95DEA89FFA7E27A31ADABA3FB11FF26" box="[1167,1192,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="529">A.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B95DEA89FFA7E27A3198ABA3FB6FFF27" box="[1210,1238,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="529">H.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B95DEA89FFA7E27A31C5ABA3FAFCFF26" box="[1255,1349,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="529">pilifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, by the wider vertex, convex pronotum without lateroposterior depressions, shorter distal antennomeres of male which are much wider than long, by the different aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="13122A1EFFA7E27A37E1AA5BFCACFE9E" box="[707,789,295,321]" captionStart="FIGS" captionStartId="8.[151,212,1796,1820]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,1174,1771]" captionTargetId="figure-414@8.[151,1436,1173,1773]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGS. 16–22. Aedeagi (not in scale). 16—Anthaxia (Haplathaxia) aethiopica sp. nov., holotype; 17—A. (H.) caerulea sp. nov., holotype; 18—A. (H.) dispar Kerremans, 1898 (RSA, Limpopo); 19—A. (H.) keniae Théry, 1941 (Kenya, Kiserian); 20—A. (H.) komareki Obenberger, 1931, holotype; 21—A. (H.) occidentalis sp. nov., holotype; 22—A. (H.) pilifrons Kerremans, 1898, holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4408013" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4408013/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="529">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
) and other characters given in the key.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B96369BFFA7E27A35E5AA37FE64FEBA" blockId="7.[151,1436,151,502]" box="[199,477,331,357]" pageId="7" pageNumber="529">
Distribution: 
<collectingCountry id="F33E760BFFA7E27A347FAA37FE61FEBA" box="[349,472,331,357]" name="Zimbabwe" pageId="7" pageNumber="529">Zimbabwe</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B96369BFFA7E27A35E5AA13FE97FE29" blockId="7.[151,1436,151,502]" pageId="7" pageNumber="529">
I erroneously synonymised this species with 
<taxonomicName id="4C294D18FFA7E27A37EAAA13FC73FE56" authorityName="Kerremans" authorityYear="1898" box="[712,970,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="529" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pilifrons" subGenus="Haplanthaxia">
<emphasis id="B95DEA89FFA7E27A37EAAA13FC94FE56" box="[712,813,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="529">Anthaxia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B95DEA89FFA7E27A361DAA13FCE2FE57" box="[831,859,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="529">H.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B95DEA89FFA7E27A364EAA13FC73FE56" box="[876,970,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="529">pilifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
when I had for study only the 
<typeStatus id="54928839FFA7E27A300DAA13FA25FE56" box="[1327,1436,367,393]" pageId="7" pageNumber="529">holotypes</typeStatus>
of both species (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB84B6AFFA7E27A3471AAEFFE69FE72" author="Bily, S." box="[339,464,402,429]" pageId="7" pageNumber="529" pagination="35 - 38" refId="ref9923" refString="Bily, S. (1985) Taxonomic notes on the genus Anthaxia (Col., Buprestidae) with the description of a new species from Mexico. International Quarterly of Entomology, 1, 35 - 38." type="journal article" year="1985">Bílý, 1985</bibRefCitation>
). Now when I have had a chance to study more specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C294D18FFA7E27A31BAAAEFFAF4FE72" authorityName="Kerremans" authorityYear="1898" box="[1176,1357,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="529" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pilifrons" subGenus="Haplanthaxia">
<emphasis id="B95DEA89FFA7E27A31BAAAEFFB09FE72" box="[1176,1200,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="529">A.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B95DEA89FFA7E27A31E0AAEFFB67FE73" box="[1218,1246,403,428]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="529">H.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B95DEA89FFA7E27A31CDAAEFFAF4FE72" box="[1263,1357,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="529">pilifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
I have changed my opinion and I suppose 
<taxonomicName id="4C294D18FFA7E27A373CAACBFD61FE0E" authorityName=": Bily" authorityYear="1985" box="[542,728,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="529" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="komareki" subGenus="Haplanthaxia">
<emphasis id="B95DEA89FFA7E27A373CAACBFD8EFE0E" box="[542,567,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="529">A.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B95DEA89FFA7E27A3764AACBFDDBFE0F" box="[582,610,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="529">H.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B95DEA89FFA7E27A3753AACBFD61FE0E" box="[625,728,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="529">komareki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be a distinct species although very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C294D18FFA7E27A31CEAACBFA25FE0E" authorityName="Kerremans" authorityYear="1898" box="[1260,1436,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="529" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pilifrons" subGenus="Haplanthaxia">
<emphasis id="B95DEA89FFA7E27A31CEAACBFABCFE0E" box="[1260,1285,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="529">A.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B95DEA89FFA7E27A3036AACBFA89FE0F" box="[1300,1328,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="529">H.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B95DEA89FFA7E27A301CAACBFA25FE0E" box="[1342,1436,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="529">pilifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see the key).
</paragraph>
